 unevenly realised and distributed.Comparing these experiences with policy and professional accounts of the 'big' future of personalised healthcare, the authors show how hope and care are multi-faceted, contingent and, at times, frustrated in the everyday complexities of living and working with cancer.This book is available as an open access ebook under a CC-BY-NC-ND licence.  afunded by Wellcome Trust  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCancerxGene therapyxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aCancerxTreatmentzGreat Britain. 0aGenomicszGreat Britain. 0aPrecision medicinezGreat Britain. 0aPrecision medicine. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  acancer.  acare.  afutures.  agenomics.  aoncology.  aparticipation.  apatients.  apersonalised medicine.  aprecision medicine.  atechnoscience.1 aChekar, Choon Key, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aChekar, Choon Key, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunningham-Burley, Sarah, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCunningham-Burley, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKerr, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoss, Emily, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRoss, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwallow, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aWellcome Trustefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7